==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cross-birth
<hw>Cross"-birth`</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ocr⟧s"b⟦etil⟧rth`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any preternatural labor, in which the body of the
child lies across the pelvis of the mother, so that the shoulder, arm,
or trunk is the part first presented at the mouth of the
uterus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossbite</ent>⟦br⟧
